SUMMARY: Local Author Read Aloud: Bubbles
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Sunday\, March 29th\, from 11am-12pm\, for a fun c
 hildren’s read-aloud of Bubbles by local author André Morrow! All are wel
 come to join us in reading and celebrating this musical tale. We’ll be fe
 aturing live children’s songs\, snacks\, and an engaging storytime. “Bubb
 les” is a whimsical story that teaches young readers to appreciate all th
 e wonderful little things in life\, like playing with pets and family\, b
 lowing bubbles\, and enjoying the outdoors. The story highlights gratitud
 e in a playful and educational way!\n\nRead more about the precious story
  of how Bubbles came to be\, quoted directly from the author:\n\n" Bubble
 s is a song\, video and children's book. The "Bubbles" project began duri
 ng a visit with some of my grandkids\, Hadley Dickson\, James Dickson\, a
 nd Danica Dickson. Most of our visits include music time and taking a wha
 ck at writing songs together. On this particular visit\, we'd just finish
 ed an enthusiastic adventure making bubbles in the backyard. Afterward\, 
 during music time\, I asked them what they wanted to write about and one 
 of them yelled out "Bubbles". And the song was born. Months later\, my mu
 sic partner David J. Michalak and I began producing the song to add to ou
 r collection of music. My cousins\, Sophia Bass and Catherine Bass\, sist
 ers\, both wonderful artists\, agreed to assist us with the project. Cath
 erine is an amazing painter and Sophia's voice is incomparable. They are 
 the daughters of my cousin Reggie Bass who was my great friend and music 
 partner of my youth. So together we all created the Bubbles book\, song\,
  and video. We hope you enjoy it! The song can be found on all major musi
 c platforms using the artist's name Morrow Michalak. The video can be fou
 nd at http://morrowmichalak.com/bubbles. Thanks to Barb Schacht\, who hea
 rd an early rendition of the song and suggested it would make a terrific 
 kid's book. ”\n\n- Wishing you Butterflies\, Sunshine\, and Rainbows\, An
 dré (Papi) Morrow
CATEGORIES:childrens-book,author-event,families,local-author
