SUMMARY: Free Estate Planning Webinar
DESCRIPTION:Details\n\n\nStrategies to Manage Incapacity\, Family Dynamic
 s\, and Financial Risks\n\nCreating your estate plan\, whether it’s a liv
 ing trust or a will\, can be a daunting task. Estate planning addresses i
 ssues that are difficult to think about\, such as death\, incapacity\, fi
 nances\, and family dynamics. It can be easy to procrastinate\, even thou
 gh these issues may weigh heavily on your mind.\n\nWe invite you to atten
 d one of our upcoming free webinars so you can take the first step toward
  having peace of mind by creating (or updating) your estate plan. This is
  an educational webinar\, where we highlight some of the concerns that ma
 ny families face and how an estate plan can help. The attorneys also brea
 k down how wills and trusts differ\, and some of the common estate planni
 ng pitfalls and how to avoid them.\n\nOur goal is to provide you with the
  education you need to protect yourself and your family\, and leave a leg
 acy of peace. If you would like to set up a meeting to discuss your estat
 e planning needs further\, we offer all participants who complete the web
 inar a free\, no obligation personal consultation with one of the attorne
 ys.\n\nAt this webinar\, we will discuss several common issues and concer
 ns\, including:\n\n  * The advantages and disadvantages of wills\, living
  trusts\, and probate\n  * Protecting your children’s inheritance from th
 eir future ex-spouses\, lawsuits\, and other claims\n  * Most living trus
 ts fail\; if you already have a trust\, find out what you can do to ensur
 e that it will protect you and your loved ones\n  * How to preserve your 
 nest egg for your family if you find yourself needing Long Term Care\n  *
  How to stay out of court and avoid the cost\, time\, and stress that a c
 onservatorship can bring if you become incapacitated.\n\nAttend a webinar
  and receive a FREE no-obligation consultation with an Attorney to answer
  any questions about setting up your estate plan ($550 value).
CATEGORIES:
