SUMMARY: Butter & Egg Days Parade and Festival
DESCRIPTION:2026 Annual Butter & Egg Days Parade and Festival\n\nDate: Sa
 turday\, April 18\, 2026\n\nStep into Petaluma's flowering world of curio
 sity and delight!\n\nThe 2026 Butter & Egg Days Parade will take place Sa
 turday\, April 18. Participants and spectators alike to celebrate the mag
 ic and charm of our historic town. Colorful floats\, costumed participant
 s\, and lively performances will celebrate Petaluma’s rich history and ag
 ricultural heritage. Join in a day of fun and local pride that promises t
 o delight visitors of all ages!\n\nThe Butter & Egg Days festivities kick
  off on Saturday\, April 11 with the Opening Ceremonies at the Petaluma H
 istorical Library and Museum (20 Fourth St)\, from Noon to 1pm. Mayor Kev
 in McDonnell will read a proclamation honoring the Grand Marshal and Good
  Egg. Come enjoy this display that shows the heart of our community.\n\nO
 ne week later on Saturday\, April 18\, the Butter & Egg Days Parade steps
  off at noon and will march through the historic downtown. The parade wil
 l showcase over 100 units with approximately 3\,000 participants and 200 
 volunteers. Clover Sonoma will return to lead the Clover Kids’ Parade\, w
 hich precedes the main parade at 11:30am with a procession of preschooler
 s and primary grade youngsters and their families.\n\nThe parade is surro
 unded by a Festival that spreads over four city blocks from 10am-5pm offe
 ring a wide variety of food\, crafts\, beverage gardens\, two large kid a
 reas\, live music\, and more! This annual event aims to bring together th
 e community for a day of fun and entertainment.\n\nThe following weekend\
 , Downtown Petaluma continues the celebration with our Annual Antique Fai
 re\, on Sunday\, April 26.\n\nVisit ButterAndEggDays.com http://www.Butte
 rAndEggDays.com for more information.\n\nHappy Butter & Egg Days!!
CATEGORIES:Festival,parade,butter,local
